HEADWORD: Kobold
<hw>Ko"bold</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., perh. orig.,
house god, hose protector. See <er>Cobalt</er>]</ety> <def>A kind of
domestic spirit in German mythology, corresponding to the Scottish
brownie and the English <person>Robin Goodfellow</person>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>KO'd</ent>⟦br⟧
